title: Babri Masjid-Ram Mandir dispute: Supreme Court declines any urgent hearing, questions Subramanian Swamy’ role
text:
Babri Masjid-Ram Mandir dispute: Supreme Court declines any urgent hearing, questions Subramanian Swamy’ role Babri Masjid-Ram Mandir dispute: Supreme Court declines any urgent hearing, questions Subramanian Swamy’ role The Supreme Court of India has declined any urgent hearing in the Babri Masjid-Ram Mandir dispute case. By: FE Online | New Delhi | Updated: March 31, 2017 11:54 AM (PTI) 
The Supreme Court of India has declined any urgent hearing in the Babri Masjid-Ram Mandir dispute case. The apex court has turned down any outside intervention in the case and has questioned petitioner Subramanian Swamy’s locus standi. His role in the whole case is also being questioned by other parties. 
Further details awaited.
